# Daily DevOps Mastery Schedule (11 AM - 10 PM)  
*(6-8 Hours of Focused Learning + Breaks)*  

### Morning Routine (11:00 AM - 12:30 PM) → Warm-up & Theory  

+-------------+-------------------------------------------------------------------------+----------------------------------+
| Time        | Activity                                                                | Focus Area                       |
+-------------+-------------------------------------------------------------------------+----------------------------------+
| 11:00-11:30 | Wake up, light exercise, coffee/tea                                     | -                                |
| 11:30-12:30 | Study Theory (AWS docs, Kubernetes.io, DevOps books)                    | - AWS Services<br>- K8s Concepts |
+-------------+-------------------------------------------------------------------------+----------------------------------+

### Deep Work Block (12:30 PM - 3:30 PM) → Hands-On Labs

+------------+--------------------------------------------------------------+----------------------------------+
| Time       | Activity                                                     | Tools/Projects                   |
+------------+--------------------------------------------------------------+----------------------------------+
| 12:30-2:30 | Lab 1: AWS/Terraform/K8s (e.g., Deploy EKS cluster)          | - Terraform<br>- EKS             |
| 2:30-3:30  | Lab 2: Automation (e.g., Python/Bash script for log cleanup) | - Python<br>- Linux              |
+------------+--------------------------------------------------------------+----------------------------------+

### Break (3:30 PM - 4:00 PM) 
- Lunch + Short Walk (Avoid screens!)  

### Project Work (4:00 PM - 7:00 PM) → Real-World Builds

+------------+-----------------------------------------------------------+----------------------------------+  
| Time       | Activity                                                  |   Project Example                |
+------------+-----------------------------------------------------------+----------------------------------+
| 4:00-6:00  | Project 1: CI/CD Pipeline (Jenkins/GitHub Actions on AWS) | - Deploy a Node.js app           |
| 6:00-7:00  | Project 2: Security (e.g., IAM Policies + KMS Encryption) | - Secure S3 buckets              |
+------------+-----------------------------------------------------------+----------------------------------+

### Dinner Break (7:00 PM - 8:00 PM)  
- Relax, watch a DevOps-related video (e.g., AWS re:Invent talks).  

### Night Review (8:00 PM - 10:00 PM) → Reinforcement

+------------+-----------------------------------------------------------------+--------------------------------------------+
| Time       | Activity                                                        | Focus Area                                 |
+------------+-----------------------------------------------------------------+--------------------------------------------+
| 8:00-9:00  | Troubleshooting Practice** (Break/fix labs on KodeKloud or AWS) | - Debug K8s pods<br>- Fix Terraform errors |
| 9:00-10:00 | Community & Open Source** (GitHub, r/devops, write a blog post) | - Contribute to Terraform modules          |
+------------+-----------------------------------------------------------------+--------------------------------------------+

# Weekly Focus Areas (Example)
*(Align with the 6-month roadmap)*  

+----------+------------------------------------------+----------------------------------+
| Day      | Primary Focus                            | Secondary Focus                  |
+----------+------------------------------------------+----------------------------------+
| Monday   | AWS Core (EC2, IAM, VPC)                 | Bash/Python Scripting            |
| Tuesday  | Terraform (AWS Modules)                  | CloudFormation                   |
| Wednesday| CI/CD (Jenkins/GitHub Actions)           | AWS CodePipeline                 |
| Thursday | Kubernetes (EKS, Helm)                   | Docker Security                  |
| Friday   | DevSecOps (IAM, KMS, Trivy)              | Chaos Engineering                |
| Saturday | Open Source + Cert Prep                  | Mock Exams (AWS DevOps Pro)      |
| Sunday   | Review & Plan Next Week                  | Light Reading (SRE Book)         |
+----------+------------------------------------------+----------------------------------+

# Pro Tips for Consistency  
1. Timebox Tasks – Use a timer (Pomodoro technique: 50 mins work, 10 mins break).  
2. Track Progress – Maintain a DevOps learning journal (Notion/Excel).  
3. Weekends – Dedicate 2-4 hours to certifications or complex projects.  
4. Burnout Prevention – Take Sundays *lightly* (e.g., watch AWS tutorials instead of labs).  

